name: Information Technology Hardware and Systems Software
description: A conceptual and technological survey of the structure of distributed information systems architectures, operating systems, network operating systems, data management systems, application development environments, peripheral technology, and user interfaces.

name: Information Systems Applications
description: Concepts and production skills relating to information systems technologies, procedures, and resources.

name: Internet Application Development
description: Internet and World Wide Web Technologies. Development and maintenance of Web sites and Web applications.

name: Fundamentals of Information Security
description: Information security, including technical security issues, people security issues, policy issues, privacy, and ethics.

name: Information Systems Application Development
description: Development of information systems applications using modern application development technologies.

name: Information Systems Analysis & Design
description: Development and evaluation of information systems with relation to efficiency and cost.

name: Information Systems Infrastructure and Networks
description: Data communications standards, protocols, models, architectures, internet topics, and ethics. Components of industry infrastructure with business justification. Study of emerging technologies and trends related to software/hardware components.

name: Database Management
description: Applications of hierarchical and relational database systems.

name: Advanced Information Systems Development
description: Use of integrated development tools for full-stack systems development. Architectural planning, technology selection, user interface design concepts, and programming for desktop applications that include database persistence.

name: Database Administration and Implementation
description: Database implementation for a multi-user environment, including usage analysis, database application development, and query optimization.

name: Enterprise Applications Development
description: Advanced n-tier client/server application development for an enterprise-wide setting.

name: Project Management and Practice
description: Computer Information Systems Capstone course. Information Systems Project Management concepts. Students plan, manage and complete a major semester-long group project involving a multi-user information system application for a client.
